claim.claim-text:
1. A method for forming a contact in a semiconductor device comprising: 
a) forming a first layer to be etched on a semiconductor substrate; 
b) successively forming a low-k dielectric sacrifice layer and a hard mask on the first layer; 
c) forming an anti-reflective layer and a photoresist pattern on the hard mask using ArF lithography technology; 
d) selectively etching the anti-reflective layer and the hard mask and simultaneously removing the photoresist pattern when etching the hard mask; 
e) forming a contact hole exposing a surface of the semiconductor substrate by etching the low-k dielectric sacrifice layer and the first layer using the hard mask as a mask; and 
f) removing the hard mask and the low-k dielectric sacrifice layer.
